fields.headline: Supermarket economy brands: taste test
fields.bodyText: Cheddar cheese Tesco Everyday Value Mature Cheddar £7.29/kg The flavour could be stronger: mature cheddar should have more of a kick. But there is a touch of sour, which is nice. ★★★ Sainsbury's Basics Full Flavour Cheddar £7.29/kg The sourness is there but it's lacking any real flavour. Although it's less salty than the others, which is good. ★★ Waitrose Essential English Cheddar 180g, £1.59 This is too salty, so salty that it's by far the strongest flavour that's coming through. ★★ The Co-operative Simply Value Mild White Cheddar 800g, £5.88 Definitely a mild cheddar. It's too mild though, so there's not nearly enough flavour. ★★ Tomato soup Waitrose Essential Cream of Tomato Soup 400g, 59p Oh this is nice! It's very rich and tastes like it has butter in it. ★★★★ Sainsbury's Basics Creamed Tomato Soup 400g, 24p A velvety smooth soup. I can actually taste the tomatoes in it too. ★★★ Tesco Everyday Value Tomato Soup 400g, 24p This one has a lovely smooth texture but I'm not really getting much of the tomatoes coming through. ★★ Morrisons M Savers Tomato Soup 400gp, 30p This one has a good flavour but unfortunately it's far too sour. ★★ Sausages Tesco Everyday Value 8 Pork Sausages 454g, 61p These are well-seasoned so have a really rich flavour. They also have a chewy outside, which I like. ★★★★ Morrisons M Savers 20 Thick Sausages 1kg, £1 These are very nice. There's not as much flavour but they have a lovely texture. ★★★ Budgens Daily Basics 8 Sausages 454g, £1.09 Not much flavour going on here but with a bit of ketchup you'd never know. ★★ Waitrose Essential British Pork Sausages 454g, £1.39 Salty, far too salty; it's all I can taste. Not good. ★ Strawberry jam Waitrose Essential Strawberry Jam 454g, 80p I really like this one: it's fruity, rich and not too sweet. BEST BUY ★★★★ Tesco Everyday Value Strawberry Jam 454g, 35p This isn't bad – you can actually taste the strawberries. ★★★ Sainsbury's Basics Strawberry Jam 454g, 29p This is both sweet and sour. Would be good with pork, I'm not sure about on toast though. ★★ Morrisons M Savers Strawberry Jam 454g, 60p Super sweet, and not in a good way. Not sure there's any fruit going on in here. ★ Baked beans Marks & Spencer Simply Value Baked Beans 410g, 41p Definitely my favourite. The sauce is nice and rich and the beans aren't too grainy. ★★★★ Tesco Everyday Value Baked Beans 420g, 28p These aren't quite as tomatoey as I would like but the beans are OK. ★★★ The Co-operative Simply Value Baked Beans 410g, 28p The beans are a lovely texture but they are pretty flavourless. ★★ Sainsbury's Basics Beans in Tomato Sauce 420g, 28p The beans are bigger, which is good but the flavour is bad, and tastes slightly astringent. ★ Sliced bread Waitrose Essential White Medium Sliced Bread 800g, 80p Best of a bad bunch, only because it's less salty, but none of these loaves really seem like bread to me. ★ Sainsbury's Basics White Sliced Bread 800g, 50p Completely tasteless, though no more than the rest of them. ★ Tesco Everyday Value Sliced White Bread 800g, 47p The dough is awful, sour and claggy. no stars Morrisons M Savers White Loaf 800g, 50p This is horrendous. I don't know what else to say. no stars Lorraine Pascale's Fast, Fresh and Easy Food (RRP £20) is available for £16 with free UK p&p fromthe Guardian Bookshop
